<h4 id="singular-value-decompositionsvd">Singular Value Decomposition(SVD)</h4>
<p>SVD means decomposition matrix transformation into three parts, which includes rotation, elongation, and projection.</p>

<ol>
  <li>diagonal matrix: elongation</li>
  <li>orthogonal matrix: rotation</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="3-galois">3. Galois</h4>
<ol>
  <li>We know a matrix can be factorized by smaller dimensional matrix.</li>
  <li>Here the user-item matrix is very sparse, most of the entries are unkown,
because evey a movie favourite may only see some of them.</li>
  <li>So we canâ€™t get factorized matrix directy, we have to learn it.</li>
</ol>

